Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper focuses on the performance analysis of NOMA-based cooperative relaying systems, which involves the study of information transmission and processing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication systems, which are an important aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.COMM (Computer Communications and Networks) - The paper discusses the performance of wireless communication systems, which is a key area of research in computer communications and networks. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an analytical framework to evaluate the performance of the system, which involves the study of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although not the primary focus, the paper mentions the use of Monte Carlo simulations to validate the analytical results, which is a common technique in multimedia research.
